description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to join a growing team and be part of a new development for those who have a diagnosis of personality disorder and complex emotional needs?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a result of the extra investment that is coming into Mental health services as part of the NHS Long term Plan, we are excited to be able to expand and transform what we offer to this service user group and their families. We are in the process of recruiting a senior MDT that will shape and drive these changes. This investment will allow us to strengthen our teams across Nottinghamshire and Bassetlaw and forms the first part of a larger expansion across all elements of our developing stepped care integrated model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be a Peer Support Worker for Personality Disorder services working as part of an MDT that provides direct clinical work, managerial and clinical supervision and training. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have a lived experience of mental distress and recovery and identify with the difficulties often associated with the diagnosis of personality disorder. You will be enthusiastic about developing the role of the Peer Support Worker within a new team and be keen to take on new challenges and ways of working. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of a team that will oversee the development of and support to personality disorder services in line with national guidance. You will be part of AMH services and contribute to developing the Peer role within our stepped model of care. You will report to the Team Leader and join a strong senior team delivering this exciting new development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to have an informal conversation, please contact Andrea Cockram, Nurse Consultant AMH or Emma Watson, Peer Support Lead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: andrea.cockram@nottshc.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone: 0115 9691300 ext. 12663&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: Emma.Watson@nottshc.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
